headline: The market's trade war roller coaster rides on. Here's what to watch next
summary: Wall Street staged a dramatic rebound Wednesday after President Donald Trump abruptly hit pause on sweeping tariffs for most countries. The 90-day delay — announced shortly after the duties took effect — whipsawed stocks and rocked major indices.

headline: The Stock Market May Fall Sharply on April 10 and April 11. Here's What Investors Should Know.
summary: The S&P 500 (SNPINDEX: ^GSPC) has tumbled 18% from the record high it reached less than two months ago, putting the benchmark index deep in market correction territory.  Investors will get some important information on April 10 and April 11 that should provide insight into the state of the economy.  On Thursday, April 10, at 8:30 a.m. ET, the Labor Department will announce Consumer Price Index (CPI) data for March.
